Description:
CloudApp enables the workplace to be more productive, helping our 4 million users share quick videos & shareable images to get their point across. Rather than writing out a long email, or message, just capture your screen & share it as a video or image link instead. 
Over 4 million users at 10s of thousands of companies like Salesforce, Uber, Adobe, Zendesk, Atlassian, Slack, Shopify, Zillow, Hubspot, SproutSocial, Outreach, and more trust CloudApp to power their modern workplace. With CloudApp, customers experienced higher customer happiness, deals closed faster, expectations communicated more clearly, and accelerated employee ramp-times. 
Founded in 2015, CloudApp has raised over $10 million from top tier investors including Adobe, SAP, Kickstart, Cervin, and Bloomberg Beta. 
About the role: 

CloudApp's Frontend team is responsible for bringing joy to users using web technology and making positive impacts. The main goals of the team are to drive CloudApp's core user experience, user growth, front-end infra/tooling, as well as complete cross functional operations. Our team works on different products, including: 
 Building www.getcloudapp.com & our content management & sharing page UI at https://share.getcloudapp.com/dashboard. You will be working on pages directly seen by millions of users on a monthly basis, and you personally will have the ability to own the direction we take. The sharing page is being shared across various systems (mobile, desktop of various types) and is used to display videos, screenshots, documents, etc. 
 We focus on core web vitals to improve user experience, as well improve information architecture to benefit SEO; 
 Creating and managing various internal web applications which are critical to CloudApps growth and ecosystem. 
As a member of CloudApp's Frontend team, you will: 

 Work closely with product and design to deliver state of the art user experience in the above products mentioned; 
 Build world-class frontends, which combine usability, accessibility, elegance, performance, and maintainability; 
 Adopt automated and manual test strategies to ensure product quality; 
 Learn and understand how CloudApp product works and help build end-to-end solutions; 
 Learn and grow from working with great colleagues and taking on challenges; 
 Help our team grow from your expertise, experience, and perspectives. 

 Qualifications: 

 BA/BS Degree in Computer Science or related major, 2+ years of industry experience in a software development environment; 
 Proficiency in Javascript, ES5/6, CSS, and various layouts; 
 Experience in solving CSS/JS multi-browser compatibility problems and front-end performance optimization; 
 Understanding of construction and continuous integration, familiarity with at least one construction tool; 
 Understanding of component-based development, familiarity with React,, Vue.js, or any other equivalent library / framework; 
 Understanding of back-end technologies and databases is a plus. 


About our Work Environment 

We have all the usual perks and benefits but what we can really offer you is a fantastic work environment powered by an amazing team. 

 Medical, dental, and vision insurance 
 401K program to help you invest in your future 
 Flexible vacation time to promote a healthy work-life balance 
 Paid parental leave to support you and your family 
 Competitive compensation and equity package 
 Location: Remote 


To help us get a better understanding of you and to stick out in the crowd of applicants, please feel free to submit an optional intro video of yourself at https://recorder.getcloudapp.com 
CloudApp is an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. In fact we are confident that the most inclusive and diverse teams accomplish the most extraordinary results.

